Package stincmale.ratmex.meter

Class AbstractNavigableMapRateMeter<C extends ConcurrentRateMeterConfig>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stincmale.ratmex.meter.AbstractRateMeter<java.lang.Void,C>
      • stincmale.ratmex.meter.AbstractNavigableMapRateMeter<C>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - A type of the configuration.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Configurable<C>, RateMeter<C>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcurrentNavigableMapRateMeter, NavigableMapRateMeter

    public abstract class AbstractNavigableMapRateMeter<C extends ConcurrentRateMeterConfig>
extends AbstractRateMeter<java.lang.Void,C>
    This is an almost complete implementation of AbstractRateMeter which only requires a correct parameters to be provided to the constructor. Depending on the arguments the constructed object can be either sequential, or concurrent.

    This implementation of RateMeter uses a NavigableMap to store and access a samples history.

    Advantages

    • Unlike AbstractRingBufferRateMeter, this implementation tolerates a large ratio of AbstractRateMeter.getSamplesInterval() to AbstractRateMeter.getTimeSensitivity(). The reason for this is that it only creates objects representing samples when necessary, hence potentially reduces the number of samples that must be added up to count the current ticks.

    Disadvantages

    • Unlike AbstractRingBufferRateMeter, this implementation produces garbage.
    • Unlike AbstractRingBufferRateMeter, this implementation does not benefit from the idea of memory locality of data.

      • AbstractNavigableMapRateMeter

        protected AbstractNavigableMapRateMeter​(long startNanos,
                                        java.time.Duration samplesInterval,
                                        C config,
                                        java.util.function.Supplier<? extends java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.Long,TicksCounter>> samplesHistorySupplier,
                                        boolean sequential)
        Parameters:
        startNanos - A starting point that is used to calculate elapsed time in nanoseconds (tNanos).
        samplesInterval - A size of the samples window. Must not be null, see RateMeter for valid values.
        config - An additional configuration. Must not be null.
        samplesHistorySupplier - A supplier providing an object that will be used to store and access the samples history. The NavigableMap provided by this supplier must use NanosComparator as comparator, and must be thread-safe if sequential argument is false. If these constraints are violated, then the behavior is unspecified.
        sequential - Specifies whether the RateMeter must be thread-safe (will be used concurrently, so the value is false), or not (will be used sequentially, so the value is true).

        Description copied from interface: RateMeter
        Instant that corresponds to the right border of the samples window. At the very beginning this is equal to RateMeter.getStartNanos(). This border can be moved to the right via RateMeter.tick(long, long) method.
        Returns:
        The rightmost registered instant.

      • rate

        public final long rate​()
        Description copied from interface: RateMeter
        Calculates the current rate of ticks measured in samplesInterval-1. Conceptually, the returned value is equal to rate(RateMeter.rightSamplesWindowBoundary()), but with both methods RateMeter.rightSamplesWindowBoundary() and RateMeter.rate(long) executed atomically.
        Returns:
        The current rate of ticks.

      • tick

        public final void tick​(long count,
                       long tNanos)
        Description copied from interface: RateMeter
        Registers a sample of count ticks at tNanos instant. If tNanos is greater than current RateMeter.rightSamplesWindowBoundary() then this method moves the samples window such that its right boundary is at tNanos.
        Parameters:
        count - Number of ticks. May be negative, zero, or positive. If zero then the method does nothing, otherwise adds count to the currently registered number of ticks at the specified instant, or just remembers count ticks if no ticks were registered at the specified instant.
        tNanos - An instant (a pair (startNanos, elapsedNanos)) at which count ticks need to be registered.

      • rateAverage

        public final double rateAverage​(long tNanos)
        Description copied from interface: RateMeter
        Calculates an average (mean) rate of ticks (measured in samplesInterval-1) from the start till the tNanos, if tNanos is greater than RateMeter.rightSamplesWindowBoundary(), otherwise returns RateMeter.rateAverage().
        Parameters:
        tNanos - An effective (imaginary) right boundary of the samples window.
        Returns:
        Average rate of ticks or 0 if tNanos is equal to RateMeter.getStartNanos().
